== English ==

=== Pronunciation ===

* skflô, skôf-

=== Etymology ===

Coined simultaneously by Mr Henry Irving Dale and Miss Kate L. Butler for a contest held in Boston in [[1923]] in which a word for "a lawless drinker of illegally made or illegally obtained liquor" was sought during the [[w:Prohibition|Prohibition]] era.<ref>Quinion, Michael, World Wide Words, http://www.worldwidewords.org/weirdwords/ww-sco2.htm</ref>

=== Noun ===

{{en-noun-reg}}

# One who habitually violates the law or fails to answer court summonses.
# A contemptuous law violator

